  "body": "***Type***: \r\n\r\n***Summary***: UserA was on non-Mainnet network(POA/xDAI/Ropset/Rinkeby). If to log out of UserA -> recover/create another account UserB -> UserB is stick to network UserA was set at some places:\r\n- transaction fee display non-Mainnet fees\r\n- TX history is not-Mainnet\r\n- Fiat values refer to non-Mainnet (on the main Wallet screen, send/request)\r\n- try to add contact by ENS name (it won't find this account because for this it looks in different network)\r\n\r\n\r\nHowever, sending ETH/assets by UserB - uses Mainnet network: I bought cryptokitty fine and Send token in 1-1 chat, - even TX fee was xDAI\r\nAfter user re-logins to account - Mainnet is used as expected on all places.\r\n\r\nNOTE: can't reproduce if to switch between accounts with different networks. It happens when second account is created/recovered.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nMainnet applied everywhere: TX fee, TX history, fiat conversion to the account which created/recovered after logout from account used NON-Mainnet network\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nPOA/xDAI/Rinkeby/Ropsten are applied in TX fee values, TX history, fiat conversion by the account which created/recovered (and connected to Mainnet by default) after logout from account used POA/xDAI/Rinkeby/Ropsten  network\r\n<img width=\"343\" alt=\"Screenshot 2019-05-22 at 20 53 32\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/58196876-dda48080-7cd3-11e9-94bd-c36846c591ae.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create new account (UserA) \r\n- UserA switches to POA/xDAI/Ropsten/Rinkeby network\r\n- UserA logs in to account\r\n- UserA logs out of account\r\n- Recover an account (or create a new one). It's UserB.\r\n- UserB checks whether USD conversion is applied according to Mainnet on main `Wallet` screen\r\n- UserB checks whether it's possible to add ENS name\r\n- UserB checks whether Wallet -> Send -> Transaction Fee display Mainnet values\r\n- UserB adds any contact and sends `/send SNT 0`  checks whether USD value\r\n\r\n**Actual result**: For the last four items:\r\n- UserA's network applied to USD conversion on Wallet main screen\r\n- ENS name not found\r\n- UserA's network applied to Transaction Fee\r\n- UserA's network applied to fiat conversion in `/send`/`/request`\r\n\r\n**Expected result:** \r\n- Mainnet applied to USD conversion on Wallet main screen\r\n- ENS name is added fine\r\n- Mainnet in Transaction Fee\r\n- Mainnet applied to fiat conversion in `/send`/`/request`\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Develop 0.11.0 (UPDATE: confirmed with Release 0.12.2 build - issue is present)\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\nLogs for scenario when user UserA logged out and UserB created (because that's the place where we should apply Mainnet everywhere\r\n[logcatRopstenOnMainnetInRequest.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2985043/RopstenVSMainnet3.log)\r\nGeth.log i've set to DEBUG when UserA created, but issue appears on UserB side until I relogin, so UserB part there is set to use INFO level by default: \r\n[geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2985044/geth.log)",
